3. What is the diff between hostname -I and hostname -i?
- hostname -I is used to display all ip addresses, 
when executing hostname -I we can see the “inet” from “ens33” i,e 192.168.46.128
 
 

-  hostname -i is used to display ip address mapped only to our hostname, when executing hostname -i we can see the “inet” from “lo” i,e 127.0.1.1
 
 


